<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17571207-21">
               <interp inst="t17571207-21" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17571207-21" type="year" value="1757"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17571207-21" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17571207"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17571207-21" type="date" value="17571207"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17571207-21-off108-c169" targOrder="Y" targets="t17571207-21-defend206 t17571207-21-off108 t17571207-21-verdict110"></join>
         
               <p>26. ( M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17571207-21-defend206" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Rose 
                  <interp inst="t17571207-21-defend206" type="surname" value="Rose"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-defend206" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-defend206" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17571207-21-off108" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-off108" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-off108" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one silver watch, value 30 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17571207-21-victim208" type="victimName">
                     James 
                     Hurd 
                  <interp inst="t17571207-21-victim208" type="surname" value="Hurd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-victim208" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-victim208" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17571207-21-off108 t17571207-21-victim208"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17571207-21-cd109" type="crimeDate">Nov. 7</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17571207-21-off108 t17571207-21-cd109"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17571207-21-person209">
                  James 
                  Hurd 
               <interp inst="t17571207-21-person209" type="surname" value="Hurd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person209" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person209" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I left my watch in my bed chamber on Monday morning, the 7th of November, and missed it about an hour after. I took up the prisoner on suspicion, and before the justice he own'd he had taken and pawn'd it at one Mr. Coy's, where I went and found it.</p>
               <p>Q. What are you?</p>
               <p>Hurd. I am a hostler out of place; the prisoner and I lodged both in one house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17571207-21-person210">
                  William 
                  Ward 
               <interp inst="t17571207-21-person210" type="surname" value="Ward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person210" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person210" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to Mr. Coy, a pawnbroker, in Leather-Lane. The prisoner pawn'd this watch to me. (Producing one, and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175712070013"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t17571207-21-person211">
                  James 
                  Newhouse 
               <interp inst="t17571207-21-person211" type="surname" value="Newhouse"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person211" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-person211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the prisoner own he had taken this watch, and pawned it in Leather-Lane.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I have had the misfortune to lose my arm, and am destitute of friends; I never did such a thing before, and hope you will pardon me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17571207-21-verdict110" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-verdict110" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17571207-21-punish111" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17571207-21-punish111" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17571207-21-defend206 t17571207-21-punish111"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
